---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const seo = {
  title: '10 Best Content Optimization Tools in 2026 (We Tested Them)',
  description: 'We tested the best content optimization tools for SEO scoring, NLP analysis, and SERP-based optimization. Ranked by real results, not vendor claims.',
  canonical: 'https://thestacc.com/best/content-optimization-tools/',
  ogImage: '/og/best/content-optimization-tools.png',
  schemaData: [
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://thestacc.com/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Best", "item": "https://thestacc.com/best/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Best Content Optimization Tools", "item": "https://thestacc.com/best/content-optimization-tools/" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "ItemList",
      "name": "10 Best Content Optimization Tools in 2026",
      "itemListOrder": "https://schema.org/ItemListOrderDescending",
      "numberOfItems": 10,
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "theStacc", "url": "https://thestacc.com/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Surfer SEO" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Clearscope" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Frase" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 5, "name": "NeuronWriter" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 6, "name": "MarketMuse" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 7, "name": "SEO.AI" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 8, "name": "Outranking" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 9, "name": "Semrush ContentShake AI" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 10, "name": "GrowthBar" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the best content optimization tool in 2026?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "theStacc is the best content optimization tool for businesses that want optimized content published automatically — 30 SEO-optimized articles per month at a 92% average score across 3,500+ published articles for $99/mo. For teams that write their own content and want an optimization layer, Surfer SEO is the best standalone tool with real-time NLP scoring from $89/mo." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What does a content optimization tool do?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Content optimization tools analyze top-ranking pages for a keyword and score your content against what's already winning in the SERPs. They extract NLP terms Google associates with a topic, evaluate word count, heading structure, and topic coverage, then score your article and surface what to add. The goal: content that matches search intent instead of hoping for the best." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How much do content optimization tools cost?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Content optimization tools range from $15/month (Frase, NeuronWriter) to $399/month (MarketMuse enterprise). Surfer SEO starts at $89/month. Clearscope starts at $170/month. theStacc includes built-in content optimization — keyword targeting, NLP scoring, header structure, meta tags — in the $99/month plan that also publishes 30 articles per month." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How does NLP-based content optimization differ from keyword density?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Keyword density optimization (repeat the keyword X times) is outdated and penalized. NLP-based optimization analyzes which topics, entities, and related terms appear across all top-ranking pages for a query, then scores your article on whether you cover those topics thoroughly. Google doesn't reward keyword repetition — it rewards comprehensive topic coverage. All tools on this list use NLP, not keyword density." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What content optimization score should I target?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "On Surfer SEO, target 70+ on the 0–100 scale. On Clearscope, target B or higher on the A–F scale. On Frase, target 75+. Articles consistently hitting these thresholds outperform unoptimized content on competitive keywords. theStacc maintains a 92% average SEO score across 3,500+ articles published monthly — the benchmark we use internally." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Can content optimization tools replace keyword research?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Partially. Most content optimization tools include some keyword research capability — Frase and Surfer's Topical Map feature are the strongest. But deep keyword research (search volume, difficulty, business intent scoring across thousands of keywords) still requires a dedicated tool like Semrush or Ahrefs. Content optimization and keyword research solve different problems and work best together." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the best budget content optimization tool?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "NeuronWriter at $23–$57/month is the best budget content optimization tool with NLP scoring. Frase at $15/month is the cheapest with real SERP-based optimization. For businesses that want content optimization without doing the writing themselves, theStacc at $99/month publishes 30 optimized articles monthly — the lowest cost per optimized, published article in the category." }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
};
---
<BaseLayout seo={seo}>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="hero-section">
    <a href="/best/" class="hero-pill">
      <span class="pill-dot"></span>
      <span>Best of 2026 · Updated Q2 2026</span>
      <span class="pill-arrow">→</span>
    </a>
    <h1 class="h-display">10 Best <span class="accent">Content Optimization Tools</span> in 2026 (We Tested Them)</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">We tested 10 content optimization tools for NLP accuracy, content scoring, and SERP-based recommendations — on real competitive keywords. Ranked by what actually correlates with ranking improvement, not feature lists or vendor claims. We publish 3,500+ articles per month with a 92% average SEO score. We know what moves the needle.</p>
    <div class="hero-ctas">
      <a href="/checkout/" class="btn btn-primary"><span>Try the #1 pick — $1 trial <span class="arrow">→</span></span></a>
      <a href="#ranked-list" class="btn btn-secondary">See the full ranking</a>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-meta">
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span><strong>10 tools</strong> tested on real competitive keywords</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span><strong>92% avg SEO score</strong> across our 3,500+ monthly articles</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span>Last updated <strong>Q2 2026</strong></span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- QUICK VERDICT -->
  <section class="modules-bento">
    <div class="modules-tabs-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Quick verdict · 3 picks</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">If you only read one section, <span class="accent">read this one.</span></h2>
      <p class="lede">Three picks for three buyer types. Full ranked list below.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bento-grid">
      <a class="bento-card bento-feature" href="/checkout/">
        <div class="bento-num">01</div>
        <div class="bento-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polygon points="12 2 15.09 8.26 22 9.27 17 14.14 18.18 21.02 12 17.77 5.82 21.02 7 14.14 2 9.27 8.91 8.26 12 2"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Overall winner: theStacc</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">The only tool that delivers <span class="accent">optimization already baked in</span> — 30 optimized, published articles per month at a 92% average SEO score.</h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">Every other tool on this list helps you optimize content you still have to write. theStacc writes and publishes the content for you, with SEO optimization built into every article. Keywords, NLP terms, meta tags, headers, internal links — all handled. 30 articles per month, $99/mo.</p>
        <ul class="bento-list">
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>92% average SEO score across 3,500+ articles/month</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Optimization built in — no separate tool or workflow needed</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Publishes to WordPress, Webflow, Ghost — direct CMS delivery</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>$1 trial · No contract · Cancel anytime</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="bento-mock">
          <div class="bento-mock-bar">
            <div class="bento-mock-meta">THESTACC · #1 OVERALL · $99/MO</div>
            <span class="bento-mock-pulse"></span>
          </div>
          <div class="bento-mock-title">92% avg SEO score · 30 articles/month · Published automatically</div>
          <div class="bento-mock-tags">
            <span class="bento-mock-tag brand">$99/mo</span>
            <span class="bento-mock-tag">30 articles</span>
            <span class="bento-mock-tag brand">Optimization included</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bento-cta">Start the $1 trial <span class="arrow">→</span></div>
      </a>

      <a class="bento-card" href="#service-2">
        <div class="bento-num">02</div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Best standalone optimizer: Surfer SEO</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">For teams that write their own content and need <span class="accent">SERP-backed NLP scoring</span> before every publish.</h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">Real-time 0–100 content score based on NLP term analysis of top-ranking pages. The most reliable optimization layer for teams with an in-house writing process.</p>
        <div class="bento-cta">See full review <span class="arrow">↓</span></div>
      </a>

      <a class="bento-card" href="#service-3">
        <div class="bento-num">03</div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Best for editorial teams: Clearscope</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">For content teams where writers need <span class="accent">A–F grading</span> they can understand without an SEO background.</h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">A–F content grades that non-SEO writers understand immediately. Reduces training time and improves first-draft quality across large editorial teams.</p>
        <div class="bento-cta">See full review <span class="arrow">↓</span></div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- HOW WE TESTED -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">How we tested</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">We ran <span class="accent">all 10 tools</span> on the same competitive keywords.</h2>
      <p>We publish 3,500+ articles per month with a 92% average SEO score across 70+ industries. That baseline means we can tell the difference between a tool that drives real optimization value and one that generates vanity metrics. Every tool analyzed the same SERPs. Every tool scored the same test articles. We compared recommendations, measured actionability, and tracked which scores correlated with ranking improvements.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col before">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">What we measured</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">5 criteria. Same competitive keywords across all 10 tools.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">No cherry-picking. Every tool scored on the same content.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Content scoring accuracy</h4>
              <p>Does the optimization score correlate with actual ranking performance? A score that doesn't predict rankings is just a number.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>NLP term quality</h4>
              <p>Are the recommended terms relevant and actionable, or noise? Bad term lists lead to keyword stuffing — not optimization.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>SERP analysis depth</h4>
              <p>How many ranking pages does the tool analyze, and how thoroughly? Shallow analysis produces shallow recommendations.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Workflow integration</h4>
              <p>Does it work inside Google Docs, WordPress, or your existing tools? Optimization that requires a separate editor creates friction.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Pricing value</h4>
              <p>What do you get per dollar — reports, articles, users? We calculated cost per optimized document across all tools.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ba-col after">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">What we found</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Most tools optimize content well. Only theStacc skips the writing step entirely.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Key findings from testing all 10 tools.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>NLP-based optimization is now standard — but term quality varies</h4>
              <p>Every tool on this list uses NLP. The differentiator is which NLP terms it surfaces — whether they're genuinely predictive of ranking improvement or just common co-occurrences with no ranking correlation.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>SERP depth is the #1 quality signal</h4>
              <p>Tools analyzing 20+ top pages produce better recommendations than tools analyzing 5–10. The more data behind the recommendations, the more reliable the score.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Most tools require you to do the writing — theStacc doesn't</h4>
              <p>Nine of ten tools are optimization layers. You write the content; the tool tells you what to fix. theStacc writes the content and optimizes it before publishing. For high-volume operations, that's the fundamental difference.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Cost per optimized article varies 50x across the field</h4>
              <p>At Clearscope ($350/month for 100 reports), each document costs $3.50 plus your writer's time. At theStacc ($99/month for 30 published articles), each optimized, published article costs $3.30 — with no writing required.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Audit tools deliver the most underrated ROI</h4>
              <p>For sites with existing content, optimization audit tools (Surfer Audit, MarketMuse Optimize) produce faster ranking wins than creating new content. Existing pages often need minor updates to jump from page 2 to page 1.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- STATS ROW -->
  <section>
    <div class="stats-row">
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">10<span class="accent"></span></div><div class="stat-label">Tools tested on real competitive SERPs</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">92<span class="accent">%</span></div><div class="stat-label">Avg SEO score · theStacc articles</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">$3<span class="accent">.30</span></div><div class="stat-label">Cost per optimized published article · theStacc</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">70<span class="accent">+</span></div><div class="stat-label">Surfer score threshold for ranking uplift</div></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RANKED LIST -->
  <section class="problem-section" id="ranked-list">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">The full ranked list</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">10 content optimization tools, <span class="accent">ranked by scoring accuracy, term quality, and real ranking impact.</span></h2>
      <p>Each entry: rank, price, who it's for, one-paragraph verdict, three pros, one honest con.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-1">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#1 · WINNER · $99/MO · OPTIMIZATION BUILT IN</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">theStacc — Best content optimization tool for teams who want results without the workflow</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For businesses that want optimized, published content without building an optimization workflow or hiring a writer to use one.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Every other tool on this list is an optimization layer you apply to content you write yourself. theStacc inverts the model: it writes, optimizes, and publishes the content for you. Every article is SEO-optimized with keyword targeting, NLP term coverage, proper header structure, meta descriptions, and internal links — before it goes live. The result: a 92% average SEO score across 3,500+ articles published per month. No optimization workflow. No tool to learn. No content to score manually. Articles publish to your site at that score, automatically.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>92% average SEO score across 3,500+ published articles — no manual optimization</h4>
              <p>Our articles are scored using the same NLP-based analysis as the best standalone optimizers. That score is achieved before publishing — not something you work toward manually.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>$3.30 per optimized, published article — the lowest in the category</h4>
              <p>Clearscope + writer = $3.50/report plus $150–$300 in writing time. theStacc = $3.30 per complete article, written, optimized, and published. The math is unambiguous.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Keyword research, NLP optimization, CMS publishing — all automated</h4>
              <p>Topic selection, keyword targeting, NLP term coverage, meta tags, internal links, and direct CMS publishing are all handled. You connect your site and theStacc handles the rest.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✗</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Honest con: you can't score-check your own existing content</h4>
              <p>theStacc doesn't audit your existing pages against SERP competitors. If you need an optimization tool to analyze and improve existing published content, pair theStacc with a standalone audit tool like Surfer.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div style="margin-top: 24px;">
          <a href="/checkout/" class="btn btn-primary"><span>Start the $1 trial <span class="arrow">→</span></span></a>
          <a href="/modules/content-seo/" class="btn btn-secondary" style="margin-left: 12px;">See Content SEO module</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-2" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#2 · $89–$219/MO · REAL-TIME NLP SCORING</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Surfer SEO — Best standalone content optimization tool overall</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For SEO teams and content managers who write their own articles and need the most accurate, SERP-backed NLP scoring before publishing.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Surfer SEO is the benchmark for standalone content optimization. The Content Editor analyzes the top 10–20 ranking pages for any keyword, extracts NLP terms, and scores your content in real time on a 0–100 scale. Articles scoring 70+ consistently outperform unoptimized content. The SERP analysis is the deepest in the category — Surfer evaluates word count patterns, heading structures, term frequency, and content depth across all ranking pages. The Topical Map feature builds content strategy clusters automatically.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Best SERP analysis depth in the standalone optimization category</h4><p>Analyzes 20+ top pages per query. Heading structure, word count distribution, entity coverage — more data behind the score than any other tool at this price point.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Audit tool for existing pages — the most underrated feature</h4><p>Point it at any published URL and Surfer identifies what to add, remove, or restructure. For sites with 50+ existing articles, the audit alone can identify dozens of quick-win updates.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Topical Map for content strategy clustering</h4><p>Identifies which articles to write to build topical authority, how to cluster them, and which to prioritize. Replaces manual keyword research for content strategy sessions.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: only optimizes — doesn't write or publish</h4><p>You still need writers and a publishing workflow. For a 30-article/month operation, Surfer + writers costs $4,000–$7,000/month. theStacc achieves a comparable SEO score for $99/month, including the writing.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-3" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#3 · $170–$350/MO · EDITORIAL TEAM GRADING</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Clearscope — Best content optimization tool for non-SEO editorial teams</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For content teams where non-SEO writers need to optimize without learning SEO — A–F grades they understand immediately.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Clearscope's differentiator is the A–F content grade. Instead of a 0–100 score that requires context to interpret, Clearscope gives writers a grade they can act on intuitively. The term list is well-curated — lower noise than some competitors. Google Docs integration means writers optimize inside their existing workflow without switching platforms. Higher price than Surfer, but justified for teams with a high ratio of writers to SEO strategists.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>A–F grading system that non-SEO writers understand immediately</h4><p>No training required. "Get to a B" is a clearer brief than "get above 72 on a proprietary scale." Reduces revision cycles on editorial teams.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Clean NLP term list with less noise</h4><p>Clearscope's term curation is more conservative than some competitors — fewer irrelevant terms, more actionable recommendations. Writers add fewer terms that have no ranking correlation.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Native Google Docs integration</h4><p>Writers optimize inside the document they're already writing in. No platform switch, no copy-paste.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: expensive — $170/month for limited documents</h4><p>$170/month for 50 reports is $3.40 per document, before writer costs. For high-volume content operations, the per-document cost adds up fast.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-4" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#4 · $15–$115/MO · SERP RESEARCH + OPTIMIZATION</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Frase — Best content optimization tool for research-heavy workflows</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For SEO writers who want SERP research, content brief building, and optimization scoring in one tool — at the lowest price in the category.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Frase combines SERP analysis, content brief generation, and optimization scoring in one interface. At $15/month for the Solo plan, it's the most affordable legitimate optimization tool on this list. The research workflow is strong — Frase pulls competitor summaries, question analyses from People Also Ask, and key term lists into a brief format. The AI writing is basic but useful for overcoming first-draft blocks.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Best SERP research and brief building at this price point</h4><p>Competitor analysis, PAA question extraction, and NLP term lists all in one brief. Reduces research time from 60+ minutes to under 15.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Cheapest legitimate optimization tool — $15/month Solo plan</h4><p>Full NLP-based optimization at the entry-level price. No other tool on this list offers real SERP-based scoring at $15/month.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Google Search Console integration for traffic data</h4><p>Connects your actual ranking and traffic data to the optimization workflow. Shows which published articles have the most ranking-improvement potential.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: scoring is less precise than Surfer or Clearscope</h4><p>The optimization score is a useful guide but less reliable as a ranking predictor than Surfer's NLP analysis. For precision at scale, you'll notice the gap.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-5" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#5 · $23–$57/MO · BUDGET NLP OPTIMIZATION</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">NeuronWriter — Best budget content optimization tool with full NLP</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For solo SEOs and small businesses that need real NLP scoring and competitor analysis at under $60/month.</p>
        </div>
