      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the best content optimization tool in 2026?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">theStacc is the best for businesses that want optimized content published automatically — 30 SEO-optimized articles per month at a 92% average score for $99/mo. For teams that write their own content and need an optimization layer, Surfer SEO is the best standalone tool with real-time NLP scoring from $89/mo.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What does a content optimization tool do?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Content optimization tools analyze top-ranking pages for a keyword and score your content against what's already winning in the SERPs. They extract NLP terms Google associates with a topic, evaluate word count, heading structure, and topic coverage, then score your article and surface what to add.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How much do content optimization tools cost?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Content optimization tools range from $15/month (Frase, NeuronWriter) to $399/month (MarketMuse enterprise). Surfer SEO starts at $89/month. Clearscope starts at $170/month. theStacc includes built-in content optimization in the $99/month plan that also publishes 30 articles per month.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How does NLP-based optimization differ from keyword density?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Keyword density optimization is outdated and penalized. NLP-based optimization analyzes which topics, entities, and related terms appear across all top-ranking pages for a query, then scores your article on whether you cover those topics thoroughly. Google rewards comprehensive topic coverage, not keyword repetition.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What content optimization score should I target?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">On Surfer SEO, target 70+ on the 0–100 scale. On Clearscope, target B or higher. On Frase, target 75+. theStacc maintains a 92% average SEO score across 3,500+ articles published monthly — the internal benchmark we use to verify our own content quality.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can content optimization tools replace keyword research?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Partially. Frase and Surfer's Topical Map feature are the strongest for keyword planning. But deep keyword research (search volume, difficulty, intent scoring across thousands of keywords) still requires a dedicated tool like Semrush or Ahrefs. Content optimization and keyword research solve different problems and work best together.</div>
        </div>
